  "contents": [{
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Events carry two identifiers that control how Memsy groups and retrieves memories: `actor_id` and `session_id`. Getting these right upfront makes search meaningfully better later."
  }, {
    "heading": "actor_id--who",
    "content": "The actor is the entity the memory is **about**. In most applications this is the end user. It can also be an AI agent, a customer account, or any stable identity you want to attach memories to."
  }, {
    "heading": "actor_id--who",
    "content": "Pick an ID that is stable across sessions (your internal user UUID), not something that rotates (like a JWT)."
  }, {
    "heading": "actor_id--who",
    "content": "Use the same `actor_id` across all event kinds for a given person — `user_message`, `assistant_message`, `tool_result` all share the actor."
  }, {
    "heading": "actor_id--who",
    "content": "Scope a search to one actor:"
  }, {
    "heading": "session_id--where-in-the-conversation",
    "content": "The session is the immediate context window the event belongs to — a conversation, a thread, a job run."
  }, {
    "heading": "session_id--where-in-the-conversation",
    "content": "Start a new `session_id` when the context logically resets (new chat, new task)."
  }, {
    "heading": "session_id--where-in-the-conversation",
    "content": "Keep the same `session_id` for every event that belongs to one conversational flow, including assistant replies and tool results."
  }, {
    "heading": "session_id--where-in-the-conversation",
    "content": "Sessions aren't used to filter `search()` today, but Memsy uses them during extraction to understand what's in scope."
  }, {
    "heading": "shared-actor-ids-vs-isolation",
    "content": "Memories are always isolated per organization (each API key belongs to one org). Within an org, memories are keyed by `actor_id`. If two users share an `actor_id`, they share memories — so don't reuse IDs across people."
  }, {
    "heading": "next",
    "content": "How `ingest()` returns before processing completes → **Async Processing**."
  }],
  "headings": [{
    "id": "actor_id--who",
    "content": "`actor_id` — *who*"
