  "contents": [{
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "The SDK retries rate-limited (HTTP 429) requests automatically. Everything else is up to you."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-retries",
    "content": "**429 responses**, up to `max_retries` times with exponential backoff."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-retries",
    "content": "If the response includes a `Retry-After` header, the SDK waits exactly that long."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-retries",
    "content": "Otherwise the SDK waits `retry_backoff * (2 ** attempt)` seconds — `1s, 2s, 4s, …` with the defaults."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-does-not-retry",
    "content": "4xx responses other than 429. These raise immediately."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-does-not-retry",
    "content": "5xx responses. These surface as `MemsyAPIError`; retry them yourself if appropriate."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-the-sdk-does-not-retry",
    "content": "Timeouts and connection errors. These raise `MemsyConnectionError`."
  }, {
    "heading": "when-to-increase-max_retries",
    "content": "For background workers and batch jobs where latency doesn't matter but making forward progress does."
  }, {
    "heading": "when-to-decrease-max_retries",
    "content": "For user-facing request paths where you'd rather fail fast and show an error than hang the request while the SDK sleeps."
  }, {
    "heading": "retry_backoff",
    "content": "Tune if you're sharing one API key across many workers and want to spread retries out. In most single-client setups the default is fine."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-happens-after-retries-are-exhausted",
    "content": "The SDK raises `RateLimitExceeded` with `retry_after` populated if the server provided one."
  }, {
    "heading": "idempotency-considerations",
    "content": "`search()` is read-only and always safe to retry."
  }, {
    "heading": "idempotency-considerations",
    "content": "`ingest()` is idempotent within a short rolling window — the server de-duplicates by content hash. Retrying a batch after a 429 is safe."
  }, {
    "heading": "idempotency-considerations",
    "content": "`status()` is read-only."
  }, {
    "heading": "idempotency-considerations",
    "content": "`clear()` is idempotent by definition."
  }, {
    "heading": "timeouts",
    "content": "`timeout` is passed straight through to `httpx`. It covers the full request lifecycle — connect + read + write. If a single call can take longer, raise it. Timeouts raise `MemsyConnectionError`, not `RateLimitExceeded`."
  }, {
    "heading": "next",
    "content": "Back to the API Reference."
