    "content": "Five minutes to your first memory. This page walks you through **dashboard → install → ingest → search** end-to-end."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Open **app.memsy.io**, create an account, and create an org (or pick an existing one)."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Then in **Settings → API Keys**:"
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Click **Create key** and give it a label (`local-dev` works)."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Copy the key — it's shown once and looks like `memsy_live_xxxxxxxxxxxx`."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "While you're there, copy your **API base URL** (e.g. `https://api.memsy.io`)."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Screenshots coming soon. For the detailed walkthrough (verification, teammates, rotation) see Sign Up."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Python 3.10, 3.11, or 3.12 required. See Installation for `uv`, `poetry`, and dev extras."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Put these in a `.env` file for local dev — and keep `.env` in `.gitignore`."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Send a batch of events. The call returns immediately; processing happens server-side."
  }, {
    "heading": undefined,
    "content": "Ask in plain English. The SDK returns ranked memories."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "In three calls you:"
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "**Ingested** raw events over HTTPS with Bearer-token auth."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "**Memsy queued them** and ran extraction → embeddings → indexing on its worker pool."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "**Searched** a semantic index and got back ranked `SearchResult` objects."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "And as a bonus:"
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "Every response has `.usage` and `.rate_limit` populated from response headers — you already know how much of your plan you've used."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "Rate-limited calls (HTTP 429) are retried automatically with exponential backoff. No code to write."
  }, {
    "heading": "what-just-happened",
    "content": "HTTP errors come back as typed Python exceptions (`AuthenticationError`, `UsageLimitExceeded`, `FeatureNotAvailable`, …)."
  }, {
    "heading": "whats-next",
    "content": "The mental model: what you send vs. what Memsy stores."
  }, {
    "heading": "whats-next",
    "content": "Thresholds, limits, actor scoping, reading scores."
  }, {
    "heading": "whats-next",
    "content": "Catch the right exception for auth, quota, and rate-limit failures."
  }, {
    "heading": "whats-next",
    "content": "Every class, method, and model — with parameter tables."
  }],
